Attribution

declarepy is an independent Python translation of concepts and designs from:

  Blair, Graeme, Alexander Coppock, and Macartan Humphreys. 2023.
  Research Design in the Social Sciences: Declaration, Diagnosis, and Redesign.
  Princeton University Press. https://book.declaredesign.org

and of the R packages in the DeclareDesign ecosystem — DeclareDesign,
randomizr, fabricatr, estimatr, and rdss — by Graeme Blair, Jasper Cooper,
Alexander Coppock, Macartan Humphreys, Luke Sonnet, and collaborators
(https://declaredesign.org). DeclareDesign and rdss are MIT-licensed;
randomizr and estimatr carry their own upstream licenses (randomizr: GPL;
estimatr: GPL) — declarepy re-implements their *behavior* from published
descriptions and does not copy their source code.

This project is not affiliated with or endorsed by the DeclareDesign authors.
